title: 286. How Big is My Penis? (And Other Things We Ask Google)
description: On the Internet, people say all kinds of things they'd never say aloud -- about sex and race, about their true wants and fears. Seth Stephens-Davidowitz has spent years parsing the data. His conclusion: our online searches are the reflection of our true selves. In the real world, everybody lies.
author: editor@freakonomics.com (Freakonomics Radio + Stitcher)
